					=09
<p><strong>Here you can find out what mean, median, mode and range are, whe=
n they are taught in school, and how you can help children to understand th=
em as part of their math learning at home.</strong></p>


<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"title-0">What are mean, median, mode a=
nd range?</h3>



<p>Mean, median and mode are different types of averages from a data set.</=
p>



<p><strong>The mean </strong>is adding up all the data points and dividing =
the sum by the number of data points (or total number of numbers). It is al=
so known as =E2=80=98arithmetic mean=E2=80=99, rather than =E2=80=98geometr=
ic mean=E2=80=99.</p>



<p><strong>The media</strong>n is the middle value (or midpoint) after all =
the data points have been arranged in value order as a list of numbers.</p>



<p><strong>The mode </strong>is the value that appears the most number of t=
imes in a data set.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>The range</strong> is the difference between the largest value a=
nd the smallest value.</p>



